useTypeIds":[],"status":"researched","overview":"A small hamlet in the East Hampshire district, mostly in the large civil parish of Ropley and partially in East Tisted. Charlwood lies in the Hampshire Downs on the western side of the A32, roughly between Ropley village and East Tisted, with Lyeway and Monkwood as its nearest neighbouring hamlets. The name is recorded in 1218 as ''Cherlewde'' — ''wood of the free peasant'' (Old English ceorl + wudu). Charlwood House (oldest building in the hamlet, shown on a 1635 estate map of Rotherfield Park) anchors the settlement; there was an associated brick kiln and clay pit, part of the wider Ropley/East Tisted brick-making industry. The hamlet has no shop, school, pub or active church of its own. SO24 0HA (Charlwood Lane) had 15 usually resident at the 2021 census; the wider hamlet remains very small.","character":"Working-farm hamlet with a couple of period houses and a handful of post-war additions on Charlwood Lane and the adjoining lanes; surrounded by arable downland and ancient woodland. No public realm of its own — village life is at Ropley.","amenities":["Charlwood House (shown on 1635 estate map of Rotherfield Park)","(at Ropley village ~1.5 mi:) Ropley Church of England Primary School","St Peter''s Church, Ropley (reconstructed after the 2014 fire)","The Anchor Inn, Lower Farringdon (~3 mi)","Watercress Line heritage steam railway (Ropley station)","Lyeway and Monkwood ancient woodland walks"],"schools":[{"name":"Ropley Church of England Primary School","phase":"Primary","ofsted":"Good","distance":"1.6 mi","url":"https://www.ropley.hants.sch.uk/"},{"name":"Perins School (Alresford)","phase":"Secondary","ofsted":"Good","distance":"5.0 mi","url":"https://www.perins.hants.sch.uk/"},{"name":"Eggar''s School (Alton)","phase":"Secondary","ofsted":"Good","distance":"5.5 mi","url":"https://www.eggars.net/"}],"transport":{"nearestStation":"Alton (5.5 mi)","commutes":[{"to":"London Waterloo","time":"1h 6m – 1h 18m direct","mode":"drive to Alton + direct South Western Railway (Alton branch)","source":"https://www.thetrainline.com/train-times/alton-to-london-waterloo"},{"to":"Winchester","time":"~25m","mode":"drive via A31 / A272","source":"https://www.southwesternrailway.com/travelling-with-us/at-the-station/alton"}],"roads":"A32 (Alton–Fareham) ~1 mi east; A31 (M3 to Winchester) ~5 mi north at Alton; A272 (Winchester–Petersfield) ~2 mi south"},"prices":{"avgSold12Mo":null,"avgDetached":null,"avgSemi":null,"avgTerraced":null,"avgFlat":null,"source":"https://www.rightmove.co.uk/house-prices/so24-0ha.html","asOf":"2026-05"},"thingsToDo":["Mid Hants ''Watercress Line'' heritage railway from Ropley to Alresford and Alton","Walking in Lyeway, Monkwood and the Hangers","Jane Austen''s House at Chawton (~6 mi)","Selborne and Gilbert White''s House (~5 mi)","New Alresford market town for shops and cafés (~5 mi west)"],"placesToEat":[{"name":"The Anchor Inn","type":"Country pub","notes":"Free house in Lower Farringdon, ~3 mi north on the A32","url":"https://www.anchorinnlowerfarringdon.co.uk/"},{"name":"The Pub With No Name (White Horse)","type":"Country pub with rooms","notes":"17th-century pub at Priors Dean, ~3 mi south; reopened 2023 under Charlie Kearns and Eddie Tyrwhitt-Drake","url":"https://www.thepubwithnoname.uk/"}],"pros":["Equidistant Alton (5.5 mi) and Alresford (5 mi) — Watercress Line and Perins School in reach","Two heritage market towns (Alton, Alresford) plus Petersfield within 25-min drive","Quiet downland setting with deep agricultural-history footprint","Charlwood House and the wider Rotherfield Park-influenced landscape are notable","Sub-Alton pricing compared to villages closer to the A31 corridor"],"cons":["Genuinely tiny — no shop, no school, no pub, no bus service to count on","Open-market sales are extremely rare (single-digit transactions across the decade in some postcode units)","No mainline station within walking distance — Alton or Alresford by car","Mostly rural broadband — speeds vary sharply by postcode","Mix of estate-tied tenancies and freehold; freehold availability is unpredictable"],"whoItSuits":"Country-house buyers wanting a working downland hamlet between Alton and Alresford, with the heritage-rail line for occasional leisure and easy A31/A272 access. Strong fit for retirees, equestrian households and home-workers happy with two-car / drive-everywhere life. Not for first-time buyers, who will find both the stock thin and the entry pricing well into the country-cottage range.","nearestStation":"Alton (5.5 mi)","primarySupermarket":"Waitrose New Alresford, West Street (~5 mi); Sainsbury''s Alton (~5.5 mi)","images":[],"sources":[{"label":"Wikipedia — Charlwood, Hampshire","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Charlwood,_Hampshire"},{"label":"Streetlist — SO24 0HA (Charlwood Lane)","url":"https://www.streetlist.co.uk/so/so24/so24-0/so24-0ha"},{"label":"South Western Railway — Alton to London Waterloo","url":"https://www.thetrainline.com/train-times/alton-to-london-waterloo"},{"label":"Ropley CofE Primary School","url":"https://www.ropley.hants.sch.uk/"},{"label":"Mid Hants Watercress Line","url":"https://www.watercressline.co.uk/"},{"label":"East Hants DC — Council Tax 2026/27 (Ropley parish)","url":"https://www.easthants.gov.uk/sites/default/files/2026-03/Council%20tax%20per%20valuation%20band%202026-27.pdf"}]},{"id":"cheriton-so24","name":"Cheriton","village":"Cheriton","town":"Winchester","county":"Hampshire","postcode":"SO24","hubCity":"Southampton","regionDir":"North","settlementType":"Non-City","subRegion":"Winchester","coords":{"lat":51.0956,"lng":-1.16504},"coordsSource":"postcode-outward-approx","houseTypeIds":[],"status":"researched","priceSummary":null,"councilTaxBand":null,"overview":"Cheriton is a Hampshire village/locality in the SO24 area with a long rural settlement history and close links to nearby market towns. Its setting combines historic parish character with day-to-day access patterns focused on nearby service centres. Today it is typically chosen for countryside living with practical road connections into surrounding employment hubs.","character":"Established Hampshire village character with mixed-period homes, lanes and surrounding farmland/green space.","amenities":["Core parish/community amenities in Cheriton and nearby villages.","Local walking routes, churches/halls and countryside recreation.","Broader retail, healthcare and rail services in nearby towns."],"schools":[{"name":"Cheriton area primary option","phase":"Primary","type":"State","ofsted":null,"distance":"~1-5 miles","url":"https://www.hants.gov.uk/educationandlearning/findaschool"},{"name":"Winchester catchment secondary option","phase":"Secondary","type":"State","ofsted":null,"distance":"~4-10 miles","url":"https://www.hants.gov.uk/educationandlearning/findaschool"}],"transport":{"commutes":[{"to":"Winchester","mode":"Drive","typical":"~15-35 min","notes":"Depends on exact address and route"},{"to":"Southampton","mode":"Drive","typical":"~30-55 min","notes":"Via major A-road/M27 corridors where relevant"}]},"prices":{"summary":"SO24 pricing reflects wider Hampshire demand patterns, with village stock often commanding premiums when supply is limited.","asOf":"2026-05","sourceUrl":"https://www.rightmove.co.uk/house-prices/SO24.html"},"thingsToDo":["Countryside walking/cycling on local rights of way","Visit nearby market-town amenities, pubs and heritage attractions"],"placesToEat":["Country pubs and cafés in the surrounding village/town catchment"],"pros":["Attractive rural setting with community identity","Access to larger towns without living in dense urban areas"],"cons":["Amenity choice is smaller than in major towns","Most households rely on car travel for many trips"],"whoItSuits":"Well suited to buyers seeking rural or semi-rural Hampshire living with realistic expectations about car dependency and travel to larger service centres.","broadbandMedianMbps":null,"nearestStation":null,"primarySupermarket":null,"images":[],"sources":[{"label":"Wikipedia — Cheriton","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cheriton"},{"label":"Hampshire County Council — Find a school","url":"https://www.hants.gov.uk/educationandlearning/findaschool"},{"label":"Rightmove House Prices SO24","url":"https://www.rightmove.co.uk/house-prices/SO24.html"},{"label":"National Rail stations and journey info","url":"https://www.nationalrail.co.uk/"}]},{"id":"chidden-gu34","name":"Chidden","village":"Chidden","town":"Alton","county":"Hampshire","postcode":"GU34","hubCity":"Guildford","regionDir":"","settlementType":"","subRegion":"Alton","coords":{"lat":51.14248,"lng":-0.98044},"coordsSource":"postcode-outward-approx","houseTypeIds":[],"status":"researched","priceSummary":null,"councilTaxBand":null,"overview":"Chidden is a tiny hamlet in the parish of Hambledon, in the City of Winchester district. Despite the seed-data id tagging it as GU34, the real Chidden sits in the PO7 postal area (post town Waterlooville), two miles north of Hambledon village in the chalk valleys between the South Downs and the Meon Valley; properties carry PO7 4TE and PO8 0SD postcodes. The hamlet''s name first appears in a tenth-century charter as ''æt cittandene'' — the second element is the Old English denu meaning valley. Chidden was historically a tithing of Hambledon and has no church, shop, school or pub of its own; everything is sourced from Hambledon, two miles south, or Petersfield, around six miles north. The hamlet lies within the South Downs National Park, on the police-defined West Meon and Hambledon neighbourhood.","character":"A handful of detached farmhouses and converted agricultural buildings on a single lane through chalk pasture; no village core, no street pattern. Building stock includes brick-and-flint farmhouses and 20th-century additions on dispersed plots. Effectively an outer fragment of the Hambledon parish, governed by SDNP planning constraints.","amenities":["Within parish of Hambledon (two miles south for shop, pub, school)","South Downs National Park designation","Quiet single-track lane access only"],"schools":[{"name":"Hambledon Primary School","phase":"Primary","ofsted":"Outstanding","distance":"2.2 mi","url":"https://reports.ofsted.gov.uk/"}],"transport":{"commutes":[{"to":"London Waterloo (via Petersfield)","time":"~1h 10m + drive","mode":"drive + train (South Western Railway)","source":"https://www.nationalrail.co.uk/"}],"nearestStation":"Petersfield (~6.3 mi)","roads":"B2150 ~2 mi; A3 (Petersfield) ~6 mi; A32 (Droxford) ~4 mi"},"prices":{"avgSold12Mo":736541,"avgDetached":null,"avgSemi":null,"avgTerraced":null,"avgFlat":null,"source":"https://checkmypostcode.uk/po74te","asOf":"2026-05"},"thingsToDo":["Walking the South Downs Way (parish boundary)","Broadhalfpenny Down cricket heritage trail (Hambledon, 2 mi)","Meon Valley Trail (former railway, cycling/walking)","Old Winchester Hill nature reserve","Hambledon Vineyard (~3 mi)"],"placesToEat":[{"name":"The Bat and Ball Inn, Broadhalfpenny Down","type":"Country pub / cricket museum","notes":"On the site of the 18th-century Hambledon Club","url":"https://www.batandball.co.uk/"},{"name":"The Vine at Hambledon","type":"Village pub","notes":"Two miles south in Hambledon","url":"https://thevineathambledon.co.uk/"}],"pros":["Inside the South Downs National Park (planning protection)","Two miles from Hambledon Primary (Ofsted Outstanding)","Meon Valley walking and cycling on the doorstep","Strong house-price premium for the seclusion"],"cons":["Seed data postcode (GU34) does not match reality (PO7); verify before searching","No shop, school, pub or station within the hamlet","Car-dependent for every daily need","Limited stock turnover; few sales per decade"],"whoItSuits":"Buyers chasing seclusion inside a National Park, who accept that every shop, station and surgery is a drive away and who can absorb the price premium that SDNP planning imposes. The hamlet''s effective population is so small that it functions as an outer extension of Hambledon, so household life will be oriented south to that village. Not appropriate for first-time buyers on a tight budget or anyone needing daily public transport. Note: this record''s id retains ''chidden-gu34'' per the seed CSV but the actual postal district is PO7.","broadbandMedianMbps":null,"nearestStation":"Petersfield (~6.3 mi)","primarySupermarket":"Waitrose, Petersfield (~6.5 mi)","images":[],"sources":["https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chidden","https://checkmypostcode.uk/po74te","https://www.streetcheck.co.uk/postcode/po74te","https://findthatpostcode.uk/places/IPN0014489.html","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hambledon,_Hampshire","https://reports.ofsted.gov.uk/"]},{"id":"chilbolton-down-so20","name":"Chilbolton Down","village":"Chilbolton Down","town":"Winchester","county":"Hampshire","postcode":"SO20","hubCity":"Southampton","regionDir":"North","settlementType":"Non-City","subRegion":"Winchester","coords":{"lat":51.12632,"lng":-1.47692},"coordsSource":"postcode-outward-approx","houseTypeIds":[],"status":"researched","priceSummary":null,"councilTaxBand":null,"overview":"Chilbolton Down sits above the River Test valley near Chilbolton and Stockbridge, in open chalk downland with broad rural views. The locality is best known for outdoor space and for proximity to Chilbolton village and observatory/science heritage nearby. It is a low-density rural address where lifestyle is countryside-led, with services mostly accessed in nearby villages and towns.","character":"Open chalk-down setting with dispersed homes and a distinctly rural, low-noise atmosphere.","amenities":["Limited immediate retail; practical services in Chilbolton/Stockbridge/Andover","Ready access to countryside walks and downland routes","Nearby village pubs and local community amenities in Chilbolton"],"schools":[{"name":"Chilbolton Church of England Primary School","phase":"Primary","type":"State","ofsted":"Good (2024)","distance":"~1–2 miles","url"